benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: TC01 covers successful update of bundle external key.
Non-Existing Resource: TC04 covers 404 response when bundle does not exist.
Concurrency Issues: TC17 covers concurrent updates to the same bundle.
Authorization: TC12 covers unauthorized update attempt.
Malformed bundleId: TC03 covers 400 response for invalid bundleId format.
Missing required header: TC02 covers 400 response for missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy.
Missing request body: TC06 covers 400 response for missing body.
Malformed JSON body: TC07 covers 400 response for JSON parse error.
Missing externalKey in body: TC08 covers 400 response for missing externalKey.
ExternalKey conflict: TC05 covers 400 response for duplicate externalKey.
Extra fields in body: TC09 covers 204 response ignoring extra fields.
Extremely long externalKey: TC10 covers 204 or 400 based on system limits.
Empty externalKey: TC11 covers 400 response for invalid externalKey.
Unexpected header: TC21 covers 204 response ignoring unexpected header.
Large payload: TC16 covers 204 or 400 based on payload limits.
Response time under normal load: TC23 covers performance threshold.
Accessibility: TC24 covers API documentation accessibility.
gaps: Partial Update: No test ensures partial updates are rejected unless allowed.
Rate Limiting: No tests cover how the system handles multiple requests in a short time.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios testing caching headers such as ETag or Cache-Control.
GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE guidelines: No tests cover these methods as they are not part of the story.
recommendations: Add a test for partial update to verify that sending incomplete data results in an error.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure the API throttles excessive requests.
Add tests to verify caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) are present and correct.
Consider adding tests for other HTTP methods (GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE) if they are relevant to the system.
Include additional concurrency tests with more than two simultaneous requests to validate conflict resolution.
